I think this probably falls into this category, and is an illustration of the value comments of this sort can offer:

Back in December 2007, the teacher at Barefoot Yoga Studio was accused by an anonymous, firsttime poster of touching her inappropriately.  In less than 3 months, 3 more women showed up and said that the same thing had happened to them.

Timeline:
  20071210: http://daviswiki.org/Barefoot_Yoga_Studio?actiondiff&version222&version121 Whistle is blown by users/florafloja  anonymous, firsttime editor without an established identity.
  20071224: http://daviswiki.org/Barefoot_Yoga_Studio?actiondiff&version223&version122 Second comment by users/lunestiasanchez  firsttime editor without an established identity.
  20071228: http://daviswiki.org/Barefoot_Yoga_Studio?actiondiff&version224&version123 Third comment by users/ginnymop  anonymous, firsttime editor without an established identity.
  20080109: After a brief series of deletions and reversions, comments are http://daviswiki.org/Barefoot_Yoga_Studio?actiondiff&version234&version133 deleted and Barefoot Yoga Studio/Talk Talk page begins.  Focus is on identity of the three posters, and how they posted from easily accessible places (two from campus).
   20080110: users/ginnymop http://daviswiki.org/Barefoot_Yoga_Studio?actiondiff&version235&version134 objects to deletion of her comment.
   20080111: users/ginnymop http://daviswiki.org/Barefoot_Yoga_Studio/Talk?actiondiff&version217&version116 explains that she only came forward and posted her experience when she saw she wasnt the only one.
   20080111: http://daviswiki.org/Barefoot_Yoga_Studio?actiondiff&version238&version137 Comments are restored.
   20080116: users/lunestiasanchez http://daviswiki.org/Barefoot_Yoga_Studio/Talk?actiondiff&version225&version124 explains that she, too came forward because of the initial warning comment by users/florafloja.  She feels bad because if she had come forward sooner, it might have protected florafloja or others.  She also feels that its too subtle to be reported to the police (which is probably true).
   20080116: users/florafloja, the initial whistleblower, http://daviswiki.org/Barefoot_Yoga_Studio/Talk?actiondiff&version226&version125 returns and asserts an individual identity.
  20080204: http://daviswiki.org/Barefoot_Yoga_Studio?actiondiff&version245&version144 Fourth comment by users/isthatso  anonymous, firsttime editor without an established identity.
  20090303: http://daviswiki.org/Barefoot_Yoga_Studio?actiondiff&version253&version152 Fifth comment by users/JanethN.  firsttime editor without an established identity, who later established an identity via several edits and comments.
  20090423: http://daviswiki.org/Barefoot_Yoga_Studio?actiondiff&version261&version160 Sixth comment by users/calvin2  anonymous, firsttime editor without an established identity.  Didnt happen to him, but he saw it happen to someone else, and compares it to his own experiences with physical abuse.

Note that several people also defended Robert, saying that their experiences with him were normal for a Yoga studio with adjustments.  That doesnt alter what was experienced by the six people who all felt that a line was crossed.  But it provides viewers with both sides of the story. Users/TomGarberson

